The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for predicting graspable locations for robotic manipulation, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The architecture takes RGB-D images as input, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The use of deep neural networks also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper aims to improve the performance of grasp detection for robotic manipulation, which is a key component of robotic systems (cs.SY).
